The Wiener index W = W(G) of G is defined as the half sum of the elements of the distance matrix:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ W = W(G) = 1/2\sum (D)ij\quad i = 1,\quad j = 1 $$\end{document}where (D)ij is the ijth element of the distance matrix which denotes the shortest graph-theoretical distance between sites i and j of G [31].

